  "text": "Akçaozoglu et al. [CITATION_1] examined the effect of PET waste particles as aggregate on two groups of mortars. One of them was entirely made of PET aggregates and the other one was made of both sand and PET aggregates. The result shows that the unit weight, compressive strength and tensile-flexural strength of the mortars including PET aggregates are less than the mortars containing combination of both sand and PET aggregates. Both mortars had much lower unit weight, compressive strength and tensile-flexural strength compared with reference sample mortars.",
